This paper is about a multimodal movie review dataset and the development of a hierarchical opinion prediction framework. The paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as sentiment analysis and aspect-based opinion mining, which are typically covered in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques, which are covered in the cs.LG (Learning) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of annotations and inter-annotator agreement, which are covered in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of specific categories to make the annotation of opinions easier, which could be related to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of a linear structured predictor, which is a machine learning technique covered in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
